details.name: Prince Tybalt
details.text:
*huff*
*puff*

details.name: Prince Tybalt
details.text: That heat is too much!

details.name: Captain Claude
details.text: Keep it up! Only 90 more to go!

details.name: Prince Tybalt
details.text: ...whaaaaaaat?

details.name: Prince Tybalt
details.text: This is not what I had in mind when I asked Chancellor for help...

details.name: Captain Claude
details.text: Ok, that's enough.

details.name: Prince Tybalt
details.text: At last, I really need to lay down.

details.name: Captain Claude
details.text: I see you are warmed up. Good. We can start with the main part then.

details.name: Prince Tybalt
details.text: Have mercy!

details.name: Captain Claude
details.text: I'm sorry, Prince, but time is not on our side.

details.name: Captain Claude
details.text: As you already know, Admiral Torsten wasn't able to free your father. At this point, Chancellor Irene believes that there is only one way to defeat Warlord Grim without an all-out war between Amber Noon and other nations.

details.name: Prince Tybalt
details.text: Grim was never a big fan of diplomacy. He believes, that a pen might well be mightier than the sword, that is why he carries his grand halberd instead.

details.name: Captain Claude
details.text: As long as he commands Amber army, it's going to be hard to get rid of him. Your kingdom needs you, Prince. More than ever before.

details.name: Prince Tybalt
details.text: Do you really believe I can achieve anything, when even the greatest of the Jade Twilight commanders failed?

details.name: Captain Claude
details.text: Yes, you can. There are plenty of officers, who question orders coming from Grim. It's getting harder and harder for him to keep up the sharade that King is still in control. If they see you return, there is a great chance, that they will join your cause.

details.name: Captain Claude
details.text: If we can erode Grim's forces and allies, we can pressure him to surrender without causing too much damage.

details.name: Captain Claude
details.text: And speaking of loyal soldiers, some of them contacted us, and agreed to come here to help you with your final test.

details.name: Prince Tybalt
details.text: Amber Noon soldiers really came here for me? And what is this test?

details.name: Captain Claude
details.text: I've been overlooking your short, but intense training, and I must admit, your progress is comendable. Chancellor Irene believes you migth be ready to face agains Grim's armies.

details.name: Captain Claude
details.text: But before that happens, there will be one final test. And I will be the judge of wether you are fit or not to lead your soldiers back to Amber Fortress.

details.name: Prince Tybalt
details.text: And that test is?

details.name: Captain Claude
details.text: The test is... also me. You will lead your troops against mine, in a mock battle.

details.name: Captain Claude
details.text: Your men are already waiting. They set up a camp on the eastern side of the training area.

details.name: Captain Claude
details.text: The goal of this encoutner is to capture the HQ building. It is highly advisable to capture the other ones first, in order to diminish the defensive capabilities, but HQ is the one that counts.

details.name: Captain Claude
details.text: Expect me to be there as well, defending it.

details.name: Captain Claude
details.text: There are some structures in the middle as well.

details.name: Captain Claude
details.text: Those will be highly contested. Having them should give a big boost to whichever side controls them.

details.name: Captain Claude
details.text: Any questions?

details.name: Prince Tybalt
details.text: No, but the looser is buying the drinks.

details.name: Captain Claude
details.text: You bet! Now let's get to our positions and we can start.
Capture the Jade Twilight HQ
Prince Tybalt must survive

details.name: Captain Claude
details.text: Congratulations, Prince! Well done!

details.name: Prince Tybalt
details.text: So how did I do, Captain?

details.name: Captain Claude
details.text: There are things, that could have been done better, but overall I am impressed. I'll let Chancellor Irene know of your accomplishments. She is putting a lot of faith in you, and you did not dissapoint.

details.name: Prince Tybalt
details.text: Thank you for your kind words! I think my soldiers need some rest.

details.name: Captain Claude
details.text: It was a hard day, for all of us. I guess today the drinks are on me, huh?

details.name: Captain Claude
details.text: Good thinking! Eliminating the opposing hero removes a lot of benefits for your enemy. I'll watch the remaining battle from the sidelines.

details.name: Prince Tybalt
details.text: I have been defeated... I wasn't ready after all...
